  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Animal
    Extends the Produce class to implement Animals, which are raised on the farm.
    AnimalsScreen
    The screen for buying animals in the county store.
    AnimalStatusScreen
    The screen for viewing the status of all animals on the farm.
    CountyStoreScreen
    The screen for the county store.
    Crop
    Extends the Produce class to implement Crops, which are grown on the farm.
    CropItem
    Extends the Item class to CropItems, which are used for tending to crops on the farm.
    CropsScreen
    The screen for buying crops in the county store.
    CropStatusScreen
    The screen for viewing the status of all the crops growing on the farm.
    DairyFarm
    Extends the Farm class to a DairyFarm, which has its own set of food items, crop items, crops and animals with custom attributes.
    FactoryFarm
    Extends the Farm class to a FactoryFarm, which has its own set of food items, crop items, crops and animals with custom attributes.
    Farm
    The Farm of our Farm Simulator.
    Farmer
    The Farmer of our Farm Simulator.
    FarmManager
    The central class of the GUI, maintaining game state and managing the launching and closing of screens.
    FeedAnimalsScreen
    The screen for feeding animals on the farm.
    FoodItem
    Extends the Item class to FoodItems, which are used for feeding animals on the farm.
    GameEnvironment
    The GameEnvironment of our Farm Simulator.
    HarvestCropsScreen
    The screen for harvesting crops on the farm.
    InventoryScreen
    The screen for viewing the player's inventory.
    Item
    The superclass Item of our Farm Simulator.
    ItemsScreen
    The screen for buying crop items and food items in the county store.
    MainScreen
    The main screen of the game, where all available actions can be seen.
    OutbackRanchFarm
    Extends the Farm class to an OutbackRanchFarm, which has its own set of food items, crop items, crops and animals with custom attributes.
    PlantationFarm
    Extends the Farm class to a PlantationFarm, which has its own set of food items, crop items, crops and animals with custom attributes.
    PlayAnimalsScreen
    The screen for playing with animals on the farm.
    Produce
    The superclass Produce of our Farm Simulator.
    SetupScreen
    The screen for getting the game duration, farm type and farm name.
    StartingScreen
    The screen for getting the farmer's name and age.
    TendCropsScreen
    The screen for tending to crops on the farm.
    UserInterface
    The UserInterface of our Farm Simulator.
    WelcomeScreen
    The screen for telling the player their farm's unique qualities.
